    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose to use ALMA to make polarization observation of extremely young objects in the First/Second Core phases discovered by ALMA Cycle 0 data. These First/Second Cores are embedded in the heart of an isolated dense core in a purely pristine condition, i.e., with no disturbance from surrounding YSOs and no disturbance of developed bipolar outflow emanating from central sources themselves. With the magnetic field morphology and polarization degrees of the First/Second Cores that we obtain with ALMA, we will test the magnetically regulated core collapse model based on a numerical simulation.</prp:abstract>
    <prp:relatedProposals>1. Toshikazu Onishi: 'Probing a mass/velocity distribution of a dense core at the formation of a multiple star system' with project code 2013.1.00204.S 
2. Kazuya Saigo,b 'Sub-hundred AU structure of dense gas at the earliest phase of multiple star formation' with project code 2013.1.00997.S</prp:relatedProposals>
